|----------------------------|-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|
| Soil Pollution             | Toxic chemicals leach into soil, inhibiting plant growth and entering food chains                          | Contaminated soil affects crops and animals, leading to health issues ([Unisan UK, n.d.](https://www.unisanuk.com/how-does-litter-harm-the-environment/)) |
| Water Pollution            | Litter transported to water bodies contaminates aquatic ecosystems and water quality                       | 45% of U.S. streams and 47% of lakes polluted; marine species affected by plastic debris ([Paperap, 2019](https://paperap.com/paper-on-littering-and-pollution/)) |
| Air Pollution              | Burning litter releases toxic emissions causing respiratory problems and acid rain                         | Over 40% of global litter burned openly, releasing harmful gases ([SidmartinBio, 2019](https://www.sidmartinbio.org/does-littering-cause-pollution/)) |
| Wildlife Harm              | Physical entanglement and ingestion of litter cause injury, illness, and death in animals                  | At least 800 marine species affected; microplastics found in human guts ([Lisbdnet, 2021](https://lisbdnet.com/how-littering-affects-the-environment/)) |
| Biodiversity and Ecosystem | Altered litter decomposition affects nutrient cycling and carbon storage, impacting ecosystem functions    | Biodiversity loss reduces decomposition rates, affecting carbon cycling ([Handa et al., 2014](https://www.nature.com/articles/nature13247)) |
